<P>School-ma&s;ters &s;hould be men of virtue, good <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">orals, and &s;uch as fear God them&s;elves, that they <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ay give good moral and religious in&s;truction to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ildren, and &s;et the pure&s;t examples before them. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">rents are certainly culpable if they employ tho&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> this office, who are known to be profane o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">mperate, or per&s;on<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">oul language, or giv|en
